mlxcel (0.1.0-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Added: `mlxcel run <repo-id-or-path>` subcommand. No `-p` enters
    the interactive chat REPL; with `-p` it produces one-shot output
    matching `mlxcel generate`. No model argument falls back to
    `mlx-community/Llama-3.2-3B-Instruct-4bit`, matching mlx-lm's
    DEFAULT_MODEL (#102)
  * Added: interactive multi-turn chat REPL. `mlxcel generate` without
    `-p` now streams a chat session token-by-token, preserves
    conversation context across turns, and supports `/bye`, `/clear`,
    and `/?` slash commands plus `"""` multiline blocks (#101)
  * Added: local model management. `mlxcel list --local` lists
    downloaded snapshots with on-disk size and absolute path;
    `mlxcel rm <repo-id>` deletes from the mlxcel store and reports
    freed bytes, prompts on TTY, requires `--yes` on non-TTY, and
    refuses to touch the read-only HuggingFace cache (#99)
  * Added: repo-id-aware `-m/--model` across `generate`, `serve`,
    `inspect`, `mlxcel-server`, and `run`. An `owner/name` repo-id is
    resolved against legacy `./models/<name>`, HF cache,
    mlxcel store, and then auto-downloaded into the store. Existing
    local paths are still used as-is (#100, #92)
  * Added: global model store at
    `${MLXCEL_CACHE_DIR:-$HOME/.cache/mlxcel}/models/<owner>/<name>`,
    shared across working directories. `download_repo` reuses an
    existing HF Hub snapshot read-only when no `--local-dir` is
    pinned, and never writes into the HF content-addressed layout
    (#98)
  * Added: `MLXCEL_MODELS_DIR` environment variable and a uniform
    `--models-dir` flag for `download`, `generate`, `serve`,
    `inspect`, `run`, `list`, and `rm`, with the precedence
    `--models-dir` > `MLXCEL_MODELS_DIR` >
    `${MLXCEL_CACHE_DIR:-$HOME/.cache/mlxcel}/models` (#108)
  * Added: bare model names (no `/`) resolve as
    `mlx-community/<name>` across every `-m` consumer. The default
    org is overridable via `MLXCEL_DEFAULT_ORG`; existing paths and
    explicit `owner/name` inputs are unchanged (#113)
  * Fix: harden the `mlxcel-server` legacy startup path so `-m` uses
    the same repo-id resolver and `--models-dir` store override as
    `mlxcel serve`, including the safetensors-only presence check
    (#92)
  * Fix: thread video resource caps (`MLXCEL_VIDEO_MAX_PIXELS` /
    `_DURATION_SEC` / `_PNG_FRAME_BYTES`) through a `VideoLimits`
    struct resolved once at the boundary instead of reading
    `std::env` deep in the decode path. Removes a libc setenv/getenv
    data race that made the per-cap tests flake under the threaded
    test runner (#104)
  * Fix: bind `127.0.0.1:0` directly through `TcpTransport` in the
    `distributed::pipeline::runtime` tests, removing the
    release-then-rebind window that caused "stub stage startup
    channel dropped" failures when another test grabbed the freed
    ephemeral port (#106)
  * Fix: acquire `env_lock()` in
    `require_secure_endpoint_refuses_plaintext_with_token` so it no
    longer races with sibling tests setting
    `MLXCEL_ALLOW_INSECURE_ENDPOINT` (#111)
  * Docs: lead the README "Run a model" section with the
    `mlxcel run` one-liner, collapse the verb examples, and move the
    store-root precedence and env-var detail to
    `docs/environment-variables.md`. README drops about 58 lines
    with no loss of documented behavior (#114)
  * Docs: refresh the M5 Max detailed table, README headline
    version, and benchmark report method table to the 2026-05-27
    full-sweep state on mlxcel 0.1.0. `internvl3-1b` passes in both
    text and VLM (#115)
  * Docs: recompute M5 Max decode aggregates against the unchanged
    `mlx-lm` / `mlx-vlm` baselines. Text average 98% to 99% (median
    99%, 62 of 66 at >=90% parity); VLM average 101% to 102%,
    median 100% to 101%, 22 comparable pairs (was 20), 18 of 22 at
    >=90% parity. README decode tables add Gemma 2 2B, Phi-3.5-mini,
    Jamba, and InternVL3 1B (#127)
  * Docs: reflect the 2026-05-28 M1 Ultra full sweep across README,
    benchmark report, and `model_tests_m1ultra.md`. M1 Ultra text
    99% median (64 of 74 at >=90%); VLM 98% median (12 of 18 at
    >=90%); `internvl3-1b` now passes on M1 (#130)
  * Docs: reword the v0.0.31 #86 entry to match the GitHub release
    note: the real bug was a batch-scheduler concurrency race where
    a burst of concurrent VLM requests overwrote a shared
    `per_layer_inputs` cell, not just a per-layer input shape issue

