mlxcel (0.0.29-1~jammy1) jammy; urgency=medium

  * Fix: model-owned VLM fallback state reset. Single-row CLI and
    benchmark generations, which do not carry a SequenceId, reused stale
    fallback caches between runs. A new
    LanguageModel::reset_runtime_state() hook, invoked from
    CxxGenerator::reset_with_model, clears the model-owned fallback slot
    in lockstep with the generator-owned cache vector for Gemma 3,
    Gemma 4, Llama 4, and Qwen 3.5 Next (#34)
  * Fix: Gemma 3n VLM padded prefill alignment. Gemma 3n VLM prefill
    aborted with a [broadcast_shapes] mismatch when the projected
    per-layer-inputs tensor diverged from the tile-padded token stream.
    The per-layer tensor is now aligned to the embeddings sequence length
    (pad when shorter, slice when longer) before the per-layer blend (#36)
  * Added: mlxcel-bench-decode same-process benchmark harness that loads a
    model once and runs the warmup and measured passes in one process,
    plus the matching bench_mlxlm.py mlx-lm / mlx-vlm baseline sweep (#36)
  * Docs: reorganize benchmark result reports, refresh Apple Silicon and
    M5 Max VLM benchmarks, and clarify README benchmark phases and
    quickstart (#32, #33)

